# Styling: inline styles allowed for dynamic layout

- **Do not enforce** removing inline styles from this codebase. A previous "eliminate all inline styling" refactor was reverted after it caused regressions (e.g. card positioning).
- **Card and scene layout** may use direct `element.style.left`, `element.style.top`, `element.style.width`, `element.style.height`, `element.style.filter`, `element.style.zIndex`, etc. Preserving this is intentional.
- **State and presentation** can still use CSS classes (e.g. `.hovered`, `.selected`, `.clone`) where that fits; no requirement to avoid inline for layout.
- **Theme data:** `useColorPalette.applyPaletteToElement()` sets `--data-*` custom properties on elements; that remains the single place for theme vars.
